ut handling by Thu (Mar 28); Support — monitor and apply workaround nightly; Priya — update Luis daily until resolved.\n- Next: Engineering will provide status update within 24 hours.\n\n3) Internal team sync (example)\n- Purpose: Weekly product roadmap alignment.\n- Participants: PM (Rita), Eng leads (Dan, Mei), Design (Carlos).\n- Key points: Priorities for Q2: mobile offline sync, performance improvements, onboarding flow redesign. Resource constraints noted.\n- Outcome/decisions: Move onboarding redesign to Q3; prioritize mobile offline for Q2; dedicate 1 FTE from platform to help performance.\n- Action items: Rita — update roadmap and communicate to stakeholders by EOD; Dan — create engineering plan for offline sync by next Tuesday; Carlos — deliver wireframes for onboarding redesign by Apr 15.\n- Next: Roadmap review meeting next Monday.\n\nIf you want, paste the call transcript or notes and I’ll produce a concise summary and action-item list formatted for email.",
